<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">Growth rates of population biomass during each growing season (120 days per year) are temperature dependent according to the Gaussian function 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0177778.e001" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0177778.e001.jpg" id="pone.0177778.e001g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M1" class="math">
    <mtable displaystyle="true" class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd columnalign="right" class="mtd">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mi class="mi">i</mi>
        </msub>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mi class="mi">T</mi>
         <mo class="mo">,</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mi class="mi">T</mi>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">o</mi>
           <mi class="mi">p</mi>
           <mi class="mi">t</mi>
           <mo class="mo">,</mo>
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">=</mo>
        <msub class="msub">
         <mi class="mi">r</mi>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">m</mi>
          <mi class="mi">a</mi>
          <mi class="mi">x</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo class="mo">·</mo>
        <mi class="mi">e</mi>
        <mi class="mi">x</mi>
        <mi class="mi">p</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <mo class="mo">-</mo>
         <mfrac class="mfrac">
          <msup class="msup">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mo class="mo">(</mo>
            <mi class="mi">T</mi>
            <mo class="mo">-</mo>
            <msub class="msub">
             <mi class="mi">T</mi>
             <mrow class="mrow">
              <mi class="mi">o</mi>
              <mi class="mi">p</mi>
              <mi class="mi">t</mi>
              <mo class="mo">,</mo>
              <mi class="mi">i</mi>
             </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo class="mo">)</mo>
           </mrow>
           <mn class="mn">2</mn>
          </msup>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mn class="mn">2</mn>
           <msubsup class="msubsup">
            <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
            <mrow class="mrow">
             <mi class="mi">o</mi>
             <mi class="mi">p</mi>
             <mi class="mi">t</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mn class="mn">2</mn>
           </msubsup>
          </mrow>
         </mfrac>
         <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
 </disp-formula> where the thermal optimum trait (
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">opt</italic>
 </sub>) determines the position of the fundamental niche of species 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>. The variance of the temperature response curve 
 <inline-formula id="pone.0177778.e002" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0177778.e002.jpg" id="pone.0177778.e002g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M2" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">o</mi>
      <mi class="mi">p</mi>
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    </msubsup>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, determining the width of species’ thermal niche, is constant for all species. If experienced temperature coincides with a species 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">opt</italic>,
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub>, it grows at a common maximum rate 
 <italic class="italic">r</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">max</italic>
 </sub>. The larger the difference between current experienced temperature 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic> and a species’ thermal optimum 
 <italic class="italic">T</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">opt</italic>,
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub>, the smaller is its growth rate.
</p>
